note: Put fields and methods on a single tread within classes, using table of contents.
Transform `tool-classfile` classes to the CLDC ones.
Turn the memhandle count/up down into system calls.
Have a run-time shelf for interned `String`s for simplicity purposes.
Debugging Support: In `DEBUG_POINT` add the address of the next point instruction, this way the byte code can be reversed from all of the debug point instructions.
Debugging Support: In the Thread base handle exceptions that fall out of a thread and are never caught.
Debugging Support: Add an exception fall through instruction for when exceptions cause a method to exit and give the exception to the calling method.
Debugging Support: Add an exception toss instruction to signify when an exception is tossed.
Debugging Support: Add an exception catch instruction to signify when an instruction is caught.
Debugging Support: Add information on which registers are for local variable mappings, used by JDWP.
Debugging Support: Record the type information of registers in an extra region, this will be used by JDWP to know what the types of variables are.
Debugging support: Add `DEBUG_EXTENDED` instruction which takes a variable amount of values. Used for JDWP support in SummerCoat.

Add the following tests:
 * Invoking static method of super-class on sub-class missing method.
 * Refer to field on sub-class that exists only in super-class.
 * Invoke special a constructor in a super-class, which should link to the current class (non-static call).
 * Constructor super jumping, calling a super-super class constructor should still mean the super constructor was called.
Add test to see that `ArrayStoreException` is emitted when the object trying to be stored is of the wrong type.
Move the BootLoader into `cldc-compact` so that it can be used by SummerCoat to load classes and such. This will be needed to run the launcher and otherwise.
Add checks to ensure that the correct exceptions are thrown when byte codes have exceptional input.
Add additional byte code tests to cover all of the byte codes available.
Add additional byte code tests for mixed primitive/object dup.
Make storage for static variables part of class specific static variable space.
Move `Assembly` to `cc.squirreljme.jvm.summercoat`.
Move Software Math to `cc.squirreljme.jvm.summercoat.math`.
Move Pack Files to property lists and add a version field.
Implement memory handles to store class references and otherwise.
Handle the memory handle accessing, for all data types.
Delete the interface invoke and load instructions and replace them with system calls as they would make more sense being those.
For the memory handle accessing stuff, combine the load/store and datatype making into a single helper method to reduce duplicate code.
Add a fragment to simplified pool handling, with pool based objects to store registers. Something to make it a bit more generic?
Add instructions for accessing virtual pool entries and otherwise.
Add a state machine which knows of the compiled state of registers, values, and otherwise? This might be complicated but it might make tracking the runtime state easier.
Simplify pool accesses to use a new native instruction and otherwise handling so that there need not be complicated byte codes around these. They will be similar to method calls.
